exactly as much as present ones (Ord, MacAskill) and Bostrom&#x27;s astronomical-waste argument follows: the expected size of the future dwarfs the present, and reducing existential risk dominates everything measurable. This is the stop Ajeya Cotra&#x27;s near-termist deliberately gets off before. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1VW1z4jYQ%2Fis7TDuFDCGGcL0eHT5AcF6mXC%2BTo73phAwR9hqrJ0seScZxc%2FnvXdkkQDCfMNrVo2d3n919boQYsUzYCxViY9A4O4PhcAgzzbgEqyDQ7L%2BCPnIJ86zndfuQKy3CNccc8u7ifNGHprEqhX7LXZxLAhgZkyWp5UpCEBPOADxImVZBzJlwMN1PPehCxPSC5axYxFnCpHk1nEOU2Uzj5niRMGtRL3Ju40XITaAyablcvbr3Qard88Xe7ZKPz4IY2JYUN8DgtrAxfUdcIFCoW7M5AxszCywMTRs0Un64RANKl2AaTykWliCR4obObYxVmL8YYi6DEuN3CFSSKuOIvjnQXRkiIdIRr6gZy2TIhJIICRVAdODxLb%2F%2B%2BtFRddfxKcXA0sU1ExmCikqEbSk6JdgYjYVlVkDmnnEXDe4GNoDRDRgWoS2geYdhrlQId%2BTEdBC3Kowr%2F0%2F%2FbjTzJ7AsYIUSNbPYSYvX6mPI7V6yTsjYphrYipLLJyGVWBOuiTVgFLkfSja6Qii9okylmidMF7CkJyIecPpuw9i%2F%2FHLnUyY0EyVCjnwVu6pSXoRyeoz5Y1U%2FoVZS6YQE9cn7GS5uoKk0RX2qotOErSS3WYgw%2FjLzL1xkRmXpH9wGMcoJE8Ut6r9MCEN4nkuAFFUq8BpFiuGbxet4H9yDXueD88lRiCUSkysqpIOoXLxu5eN1nVOpQdQRC2zGxJjJ73%2BX9XKu50deOqmBPoFmF06PwbXm8mUuV%2BFeII6L19%2BQ8XpzyZLowOF8E5HXI7qMJwcOr9H0KGYbiz17t9Nz1v5Hymae7pt6nudsH%2FtEYi5zLsJltjL7Pr9WPr%2F1Sh8mRISHIfTeUq4rfb7zKO0OwdtozL%2FPJ6PpP8DWqF2DpCT8nx4Gu1IL92RoebJp2q3MAkVGEiFK%2B66x6Dp7N80gzaxxaubWCStQrqGHcO%2Fq%2BwyUdxzAvDFVAUnTyQ6%2BV7qbN9qQh2%2FhDCBBJpu1wmyRArrw0t6HvOJrrFpKFPVgu5o4jvGN9AZuZFM4mrtZMPp82apH3FNRPeTo5jOcwcUGy5dWY0qDDjNtYp4egd3VXj3sjCp07WY4whTZKsN6pD2VOiTvAOlrTLMmBQqbNg7CrVb%2FUg6PlGNX2fVw30jdtDEMYRhoxhXFlEYvCShEcySRhz1Rjz6aTi%2F9yZGsveuZY%2FU4PuPrcQ9abQv84NpM0%2BRxi2wIU25sRyP1msFm%2BccobcdFs2qDNjz%2FePoBT52dN15aNK%2BWbjMNYQN07z1sundWu9tm1zdfty04gNytY07ZXr4uOGpuTiwMNeDOuqQXnMfu63PZePkfdKAEzQ%3D%3D" id="w1_3_4"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f6e0c0;strokeColor=#c9932a;fontColor=#5a3f10;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="606" y="940" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+3+4+9]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 9 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1lW1z4jYQx7%2FKDtNOIUOIIVzvQocXJHEeplwvk%2BN60wkZIuw1Vk%2BWPJKM4%2Bby3buygUAwr0K8q5%2F24b%2Brl0aIEcuEvVAhNgaNkxMYDocw0YxLsAoCzf4r6EcuYZr1vG4fcqVFuOSYQ96dnc76szNoGqtSOGu5o1NJiJExWZJariQEMZEG4EHKtApizoQDdc960IWI6RnLWTGLs4RJszacQpTZTOPq8yxh1qKe5dzGs5CbQGXScrlYu%2FdBqu3vs53Ta68zEHzprFzODE8ywVx4ZbQ%2BC2JgbyFzAwzuChvT74gLBCrFm9mcgI2ZBRaGpg0aqX5cogGlS5jGY8qUJUghc0PfbYxVEX4zlJcMSsYfEKgkVcalsXGgszJEItInbkqasUyGTCiJkFCDRAeeNvX3l08uVHccn1MMLB1cMpEhqKgkvLWqU8LO0ViYZwVk7hp30OB2YgMY3YJhEdoCmvcY5kqFcE9OTAdxq2Jc%2B3%2F596OJfwnzAhYoUTOLnbRYqwNDbneKdUTGNnXIViG5ehKpZF1yTVEDRpH7Q8VG1wilF1SpVPOE6QLmdEXEA06%2F23DuX32596kSmomSkCNfxK7nVBehnF5j%2FlT1T6iFVDohuZ15v8LFLTSVpqyPVXScsIXkNgsRzr9M%2FAuXmVFZ%2Bie3QYzykoniDvU3E8IQXqYSIEWVCrxBkWK4sXgd74O70Ot8cD45CjFHiuSaGukQlYvXrXy8rnMqFYo6YoHNmDhn8sffZb%2Bc6%2BmBm45q0EfQ7MLxIVxrKl%2BnchHuJOJi8fqrYLzeVLIk2nM4XWXk9ShcxpM9h3U2PcrZxmLH3u30nLX%2FkaqZp7umnuc528c%2BBTGVORfhPFuYXZ%2FfK59PvdKHCRHhfgq9Tcl1pc93HqXdEbyVxvyH%2FHI0%2FgfYErUbkJSE%2F8vjYFtq4Y4MLU9WQ%2Fsms0CRkUSI0r4bLDrO3u06SDNrnJq5d